1) Explain what a token is used for service authentication.
A token is used for authorization (verifying that the access is allowed).

2)  What steps can you take in your web apps to keep your data secure?
Have a password and authentication, have control over the user input, and permissions for accessing the data.

3)  Describe how web servers work.
Web server is essentially a tool/program that allows having access to the storage of files based on the requests. 

4) Which HTTP methods can be mapped to the CRUD acronym that we use when interfacing with APIs/Servers.

Post/get/put/delete
